ker": "Buddy Collette", "relation": "played with", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "he could do the drummer — Irv Cottler or somebody like that, and they’d have the beat going.", "doc_title": "Buddy Collette interviewed by Monk Rowe, Los Angeles, California, February 13, 1999", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/buddy-collette-interviewed-monk-rowe-los-angeles-california-february-13-1999"}, {"speaker": "Peter Appleyard", "relation": "has met", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "I went over to Manny’s Music Shop and I ran into Irv Cottler, his drummer.", "doc_title": "Peter Appleyard interviewed by Monk Rowe, Utica, New York, October 4, 2012", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/peter-appleyard-interviewed-monk-rowe-utica-new-york-october-4-2012"}]}